name: TheAtlantic
text: More Americans are getting sick, more Americans are hospitalized, and more Americans are dying. Almost every major metric of the pandemic stands at or near record levels, @COVID19tracking and @yayitsrob report. https://t.co/ERSMOkANEd

text: "Terms like 'negligence' and 'manslaughter' and, yes, 'homicide' are useful right now. They give us a way of assessing the horror a government is visiting upon its people," @JamesFallows writes: https://t.co/6mtCoGAli1

text: President Trump can’t and won’t overturn the election result, but he can cause plenty more havoc on his way out, @PeterAtlantic writes. https://t.co/O8kO0BCA0p

name: TheAtlantic
text: Simply starting the job of the presidency is a tremendous task, but "ensuring a smooth transition is another one of those patterns of doing things that line up with the basic ideas of the public good," @JDickerson writes. https://t.co/Ct9LW7u4rq

name: TheAtlantic
text: "This is a yes-and situation, not an either/or one: Why shouldn’t the government eliminate student-loan debt while also trying to pass another unemployment extension?" argues @AnnieLowrey: https://t.co/froh89Q4IA

text: Black men are among the most loyal backers of the Democratic Party, and they are also more likely than Black women to vote for Republicans. @LeahRigueur explores the diversity of opinion that exists within this bloc: https://t.co/QDgq3UsnrL

name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @prashantrao: "Everyone stood around the statue, earnestly discussing patriarchy, objectification, and the male gaze, plus the merits of figurative versus representational art. It was quite disconcerting. What is this, I thought—France?

But no, this is Britain."

name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @PeterAtlantic: As Trump confronts an uncertain future, he could stretch or smash the boundaries of presidential power in ways no one else has tried. He could damage the basic notion that presidents are accountable for their actions and answerable to the law.

text: Wildlife trade bans are designed to protect vulnerable species. Some experts worry that they might be doing the opposite, @ngreports reports. https://t.co/fzuVYvZ3XI
